Fibrate drugs market can be segmented based on product type, application, and distribution channel. In terms of product type, the market includes fenofibrate, gemfibrozil, bezafibrate, ciprofibrate, and others. Among these, fenofibrate is expected to dominate the market due to its effectiveness in reducing cholesterol levels. When it comes to applications, the market caters to cardiovascular diseases, diabetes, obesity, hyperlipidemia, and others. The rising prevalence of cardiovascular diseases and diabetes is likely to drive the market growth significantly. By distribution channel, the market is subdivided into hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies, with hospital pharmacies currently holding a substantial market share due to the availability of a wide range of products.

